cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on network traffic forecasting and discusses the relevance of the techniques from a network-telemetric perspective. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category as network traffic is a type of information flow and the paper may discuss social aspects of network traffic. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as autoregressive models are a type of machine learning technique. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper may discuss information-theoretic aspects of network traffic forecasting. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the algorithms and data structures used in autoregressive traffic forecasting techniques.
